# Email Spoofing Scam Investigation

## Overview

This project documents the investigation of a spoofed email that falsely appeared to originate from my Hotmail account.

## Objectives

* Verify sender authenticity
* Determine whether account compromise occurred
* Identify sending infrastructure
* Extract indicators of compromise

## Key Findings

### Sender Analysis

* Displayed sender address was spoofed.
* Return-Path did not match the displayed sender.
* Message originated from an external domain unrelated to Microsoft.

### Authentication Analysis

* SPF: None
* DKIM: None
* DMARC: Fail

These results indicated that the sending infrastructure was not authorized to send email on behalf of the displayed sender.

### Infrastructure Analysis

* Originating IP identified through SMTP headers
* Sending domain identified through Return-Path analysis
* Message source traced through Received headers

## Skills Demonstrated

* Email Header Analysis
* SMTP Investigation
* SPF Analysis
* DKIM Analysis
* DMARC Analysis
* Indicator of Compromise (IOC) Extraction
* Threat Intelligence Reporting
* Incident Documentation

## Outcome

Analysis determined that the email was a spoofed campaign and did not originate from the recipient's Hotmail account. Indicators extracted during the investigation were submitted to Chainabuse for fraud reporting and correlation.
